    Max dmg = ([(strength + weapon skill)/100] * weapon damage) + damage bonus<br>
<br>
So strength does affect the maximum damage that you will hit for, and thus have some effect upon average damage. But Ed's point is that damage in EQ is heavily centered around the modal (modal is NOT the same thing as average, modal is the number that you hit for most often). The forumla for the modal is:<br>
Modal = (2 * weapon damage) + damage bonus<br>
<br>
Note that STR does not affect the modal. Ed contends (I think rightly, though I plan to do some parsing to test this) that the modal weights the average so heavily, that increasing the max damage has little affect upon the average damage. That make sense? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=30346">Gimmel Greatheart</a> - Vicar of Kaladim<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=53479">Xhao</a> - Monk of the Court of Pain<br>
