The second zone, the &quot;loading sawtooth&quot; was what I saw and found was analagous to NPC damage. <br>
I'll repeat it, maybe it will make more sense now.<br>
<br>
The peaks during this zone occur at X values 1 through 20, with 20 being the modal damage itself (huge spike) in formula DB + X*DI<br>
<br>
The DI for PC damage is the weapon damage, in the right click info of weapons, divided by 10. <br>
The DB is the damage bonus that we all talk about, the one that's displayed on the right click info of weapons.<br>
<br>
The first, min damage spike is DB + DI, just like min damage for NPCs. The modal damage is DB + 20*DI, just like _max_ damage for NPCs. This agrees with the old formula modal damage = DB + 2*weapon damage, because DI = weapon damage/10.<br>
<br>
This accounts for hits in the off hand as well: the min hit is DB + DI. But in the off hand, DB is 0. So the min hit is just DI, which is usually just 1 because it is weapon damage divided by 10. But some weapons have high enough damage to make the min hit 2.<br>
<br>
There are some less likely hits in between the peaks, unlike NPC damage.<br>
<br>
So, your first 3 zones, except for the trash between the peaks, are analagous to NPC damage.<br>
<br>
Sorry if this didn't make sense the first time I typed it up.<br>
<br>
- Joim<br>
